Gunmen on Monday attacked a convoy of Ikedi Ohakim, a former governor of Imo State, killing four of his police orderlies. The former governor’s convoy was attacked at Oriagu in the Ehime Mbano Local Government Area of the state on Monday evening. He, however, escaped by the whiskers had his backup vehicle bombed, leading to the death of the four policemen in his convoy. A source close to the ex-governor disclosed that it took the brevity of the driver of the ex-governor for him to escape. Details subsequently…